    <!-- Narrative conclusion -->
    <div class="narrative">
      <p>The Master Archivist contemplates the seals you have placed on the chronicles. He nods with satisfaction.</p>
      <p>"You now master the art of Magic Seals. You know how to mark the important moments of History, distinguish a quick seal from an official seal, and find any milestone in an instant. <strong>This is a power that the best Archivists use with discernment</strong> - each seal must have a reason to exist."</p>
      <p>He points to a final golden tag, hanging on the wall above the exit door.</p>
      <p>"Remember: <strong>a good seal tells a story all by itself</strong>. Its name, its message, its placement - everything must be chosen with care. The Archivists who come after you will be grateful."</p>
